    <p>1ST 100 STAGE</p>
    <p>More than 100 trainees have signed up. They learn ba­sic food safety and hy­giene and how to pro­mote a busi­ness on so­cial me­dia and food de­liv­ery apps, among other things.</p>
    <p>2ND 40 STAGE %</p>
    <p>The pro­por­tion of trainees who have made it to the sec­ond stage, where they are ap­pren­ticed to ex­pe­ri­enced hawk­ers for two months.</p>
    <p>3RD STAGE</p>
    <p>Their skills will be put into prac­tice through the In­cu­ba­tion Stall Pro­gramme, which of­fers an av­er­age rental re­bate of 40 per cent for 15 months. They can also rent stalls re­leased through NEA’s monthly ten­der.</p>


